  "prompt": "What can cause astigmatism?",
  "response": "Astigmatism is typically caused by:\n\n1. Genetic factors\n- Inherited from parents\n- Present from birth\n\n2. Eye shape abnormalities\n- Irregularly shaped cornea\n- Irregularly shaped lens\n- Curvature differences in the eye's surface\n\n3. Eye injuries or trauma\n- Scarring of the cornea\n- Physical damage to the eye\n\n4. Eye surgeries\n- Previous eye procedures can alter corneal shape\n\n5. Medical conditions\n- Keratoconus (corneal thinning)\n- Diabetes\n- Certain eye disorders\n\n6. Natural aging process\n- Changes in eye structure over time\n\n7. Eye strain\n- Prolonged close-up work\n- Extensive screen time\n\n8. Developmental issues\n- Uneven growth of the eye during childhood\n\nMost cases of astigmatism are mild and can be corrected with glasses, contact lenses, or in some cases, laser eye surgery. Regular eye exams can help detect and monitor astigmatism.",
